events.body:
@practicalswift Thanks for feedback. I will look into using SanitizeString.

@MarcoFalke It is different in that you do not need to combine the logs. You can look at a specific node's debug.log output and see logprint's from the tests directly.

@promag The output from all combined logs is rather large, so having a way to see test debug log in individual node log files was convenient.

From reactions I am starting to think maybe this is not what people want, so I will close this PR unless it gets more hearts.
